value.value: An osteosarcoma usually arising from the metaphysis of long bones. It is characterized by the presence of a cystic architecture with blood-filled spaces. The prognosis is similar to that of conventional osteosarcoma.

value.value: A WHO grade III meningioma characterized by the predominance of a perivascular pseudopapillary pattern.
This gene plays an important role in cellular proliferation and differentiation.

value.value: A benign neoplasm that can arise from any of the adrenal cortical layers.  It can be associated with the overproduction of glucocorticoids (Cushing's syndrome), androgenic or estrogenic steroids (adrenogenital syndrome), or mineralocorticoids (Conn's syndrome).
